Renowned since their inception for electrifying performances, The Rose quickly became one of Korea's most sought-after groups delivering a series of critically acclaimed albums that resonated with fans worldwide. In 2019, three of the band members temporarily went on hiatus to fulfill their mandatory military service obligations, during which WOOSUNG pursued a successful solo career, releasing captivating albums and embarking on sold-out world tours.In a moment of sheer joy for their devoted fans, The Rose reunited during one of Woosung's performances in South Korea in 2022. This reunion paved the way for their first full-length album HEAL, which was inspired by the transformative power of music and the stories shared by both their fans and themselves. HEAL soared to #4 on Billboard's Heatseekers Chart, while their accompanying HEAL Together World Tour drew an overwhelming crowd of over 90,000 attendees.Now, with their highly anticipated second full-length album DUAL, The Rose takes their music to new heights. Building upon the emotional honesty and vulnerability showcased in HEAL, this latest offering explores the profound concept of 'balance.' description: Let all the secrets come out. The Morning Show Season 3 returns September 13 on Apple TV+ https://apple.co/_TheMorningShowIn The Morning Show season three, the future of the network is thrown into question and loyalties are pushed to the brink when a tech titan takes an interest in UBA. Unexpected alliances form, private truths are weaponized, and everyone is forced to confront their core values both in and out of the newsroom. Along with Witherspoon and Aniston, the star-studded season three ensemble cast is led by Billy Crudup, Mark Duplass, Nestor Carbonell, Karen Pittman, Greta Lee, Jon Hamm, Nicole Beharie, and Julianna Margulies.  The Emmy, SAG and Critics Choice Award-winning drama, which has already received an early renewal for season four, is directed and executive produced by Mimi Leder, with Charlotte Stoudt serving as showrunner and executive producer. The series is produced by the studio Media Res, and executive produced by Michael Ellenberg through Media Res, along with Aniston and Kristin Hahn through Echo Films; Witherspoon and Lauren Neustadter through Hello Sunshine. Leder serves as executive producer and director. Now streaming globally on Apple TV+, the broadly acclaimed second season of The Morning Show received Emmy Award nominations for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series, Reese Witherspoon; Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series, Billy Crudup, who also won the award for season one; and, Outstanding Guest Actress in a Drama Series, Marcia Gay Harden.  In its first season, Crudup‚Äôs performance as Cory Ellison earned an Emmy win in the Supporting Actor in a Drama Series category, in addition to a Critics Choice Award. Aniston's powerful performance as Alex Levy, earned a SAG Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series. Leder earned an Outstanding Directing For a Drama Series nomination for helming the season one finale. description: SpaceX is targeting Wednesday, July 26 for Falcon Heavy‚Äôs launch of the Hughes JUPITER 3 mission to a geosynchronous transfer orbit from Launch Complex 39A (LC-39A) at Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The 99-minute launch window opens at 11:04 p.m. ET (03:04 UTC on July 27. If needed, a backup launch opportunity is available on Thursday, July 27 with the same window.Both of the side boosters on this mission previously supported USSF-44 and USSF-67. Following stage separation, Falcon Heavy‚Äôs two side boosters will land on SpaceX‚Äôs Landing Zones 1 and 2 (LZ-1 and LZ-2) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida. A live webcast of this mission will begin about 15 minutes prior to liftoff.

He wanted to show the president that Skrulls weren't a threat which he accomplished judging off the news reports.Anyway Gi'ah and Varras part of the entry closed out with them having a shootout with Graviks forces. As for Gravik, he killed Pagon for being a Pagon and we learned his true plan. Alongside wanting to start world War 3 he was also trying to get something known as the harvest. Turned out Nick had collected the Avengers DNA and if I ever get super powers I'm completely f**ked. I wouldnt wish having to collect it on Gravik but yeah...entire room...full of it.WhatGoing back to Avengers Endgame it kinda recontextualises Nick Fury's appearance and while he was at the funeral he probably had his agents out in the field picking up the sample.

title: 7 Days In The Most Controversial BALCONY Cabin at Sea
tags: cruise|cruise tips|emma cruises|celebrity edge|celebrity infinite veranda|infinite veranda cabin review|celebrity cruises|balcony cabin
description: A balcony cabin, where the balcony is INSIDE the ship? It doesn't sound possible, but it is! I spent 7 days in a Celebrity Edge Infinite Veranda cabin, and here's what I thought. I‚Äôm currently on a cruise and I‚Äôm staying in a balcony cabin that has a feature that I‚Äôve never seen on a cruise ship before. It‚Äôs very different from what you‚Äôd expect when you hear the word balcony and I‚Äôve spent most of this week trying to work out why the cruise line made this decision. I‚Äôve seen and done some things this week that I definitely didn‚Äôt expect when I booked this cruise and picked this cabin.Like quirky cabins? Check out these!My balcony opened onto the PROMENADE DECK: https://youtu.be/Sg9NynxWReMThis cabin had a glass bathroom wall: https://youtu.be/EvhmoI-OJa8The cheapest cabin on a MEGASHIP: https://youtu.be/mKHOhGD9Tp8 Usually when you look at cruise ship balcony cabins they are pretty similar, the designs do change between ships and the layout inside might change but the actual balcony space is pretty standard. It‚Äôs usually a rectangle of some size with two chairs on it, there‚Äôs not much that can be changed with that, maybe the addition of a table if you‚Äôre lucky. The ship that I‚Äôm currently onboard is the Celebrity Edge, built in 2018 she‚Äôs the first in Celebrities edge class of ships. She was game changing for Celebrity in lots of ways and the cabins are no exception. When I booked this cruise I decided to book what is called an Infinite Veranda cabin. There are 918 infinite verandas on this ship and they are 23% bigger than balcony cabins on other Celebrity ships. I usually am an inside cabin kind of girl but I do love a controversial cabin and as I had read lots of very good and very bad reviews about the cabin, I wanted to find out for myself if I would like it. One person described it as a ‚Äòthe best room they‚Äôve ever stayed in‚Äô but another person said that it was so bad that it ‚Äòruined their vacation beyond repair‚Äô. I did have somebody tell me recently though that their cruise was ruined by the library being too cold so I always try to take those reviews with a pinch of salt. The description of the cabin promised to ‚Äòblur the boundary between inside and outside‚Äô and that it definitely did. My cabin was assigned at the time of booking and I was given cabin 7156 towards the front of deck 7. Quite often cruise lines will give you a discount if you don‚Äôt pick your specific cabin location but Celebrity didn‚Äôt have any option for that so I just let my travel agent pick the cabin, I trusted her and in the past I‚Äôve had cabins right at the top of the ship, right at the bottom, at the front, at the back, besides the atrium, under nightclubs, you name it I‚Äôve probably tried it at some point because I am not fussy when it comes to cabin location.The cabin that I was assigned looked good cabin on paper, so I was feeling pretty optimistic and excited.
